olive oil
1 clove garlic
1 tomato
1 cucumber
½ packet ciabatta
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 tsp water
1 bag Cos Lettuce Mix
½ sachet Italian Herbs
½ packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

Finely chop the garlic. Roughly chop the tomato.
Thinly slice the cucumber into half-moons. Tear
the ciabatta (see ingredients) into small chunks.
Cut the chicken breast into 2cm chunks. In a
medium bowl, combine the chicken breast, garlic
and Italian herbs (see ingredients). Drizzle with
olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss
to coat.

Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the ciabatta,
tossing occasionally, until golden and crisp,
4-5 minutes. Season to taste, then transfer to a
large bowl.

In a small bowl, add the creamy pesto dressing,
the water and a drizzle of olive oil. Season and mix
well to combine.

Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil. Cook the chicken, tossing, until
cooked through, 5-6 minutes.

Add the cos lettuce mix, tomato, cucumber,
grated Parmesan cheese (see ingredients) and
chicken to the bowl with the croutons. Toss to
combine and drizzle with the pesto dressing.

TIP: You can serve the chicken on the side if
you prefer!

Divide the Italian herbed chicken salad between bowls.